#githubRepo Clone repository (GITHUB_REPO_URL) into the local workspace. Create branch (JIRA ID] from the default remote branch and set upstream. Push the new branch (JIRA ID> to origin.
#jira_query (JIRA_ID) Explain the story scope and acceptance criteria, then implement the required changes in (GITHUB REPO NAME)
#githubRepo Review local changes on branch (JIRA_ID): run unit tests, linters/formatters, static analysis, and show a unified diff of all modified files for verification before pushing commits to GitHub.
#githubRepo Commit all validated changes to branch JIRA_ID) using commit message "JIRA_ID) - <commit message>" only
#githubRepo Push the latest commits on branch JIRA ID> to origin
#githubRepo Create and submit a final pull request from JIRA ID] to the repository's default branch. Use PR title "(JIRA_ID) - <commit message>" anc include a link to the Jira story
#jira_query (JIRA_ID) Update the story with implementation notes, attach the PR link, and transition the ticket to In Review




